posts.title: Veritas Academy
posts.text: Veritas Academy 2018 300 74      2018       Veritas China20152017Veritas Academy200Veritas Academy -  - 2018 I found many courses that would expand my interest in creative writing, such as Literary Analysis, Linguistics, and Performance Workshop. Other areas of Studies including Social Science and Natural Science would also equip me with a rational mindset when analyzing social issues. All in all, I am looking forward to pursuing a holistic understanding of the world with intellectual peers who have similar motivations. , Wooster School, Grade 11   Veritas appeals to me for that it offers an exceptional opportunity to learn about subjects that I long have interest in but unable to take. I used to complain a lot about history and English requirements because Im a strong math and science student. However, from those humanity courses, I learned necessary social and communication skills. I gradually came to this belief that every subject is interconnected. As an intending civil engineering student, its important for me to have a comprehensive background and the ability to think critically. , St.Stephens Episcopal High, Grade 12   I am going to a liberal arts college this fall, so I would like to get a taste of what the courses would be like in college, as well as experiencing learning in an English environment. Additionally, since I know that there will be graduates, current students and even professors at Carleton offering courses, I believe it would be a great chance to get to know those people whom I can surely learn from.    - 2018  Veritas Academy -  Veritas Academy 2018 |  2018 Veritas Academy 2018 Veritas Academy 2018 Veritas Academy 2018 Veritas Academy  Veritas | &  &  | Veritas  | Veritas  Veritas 2018 ()  Q&A 2018  Veritas Academy  &   Veritas 2017  |  Veritas Summer Academy 2016 Veritas Summer Academy 2015       201881-9    5500 9 4500 contact@veritaschina.org  veritaschina.org/  201871   contact@veritaschina.org  veritaschina @VeritasChina

posts.title: Build the "Tunnel"
posts.excerpt: Access be blocked by the GFW?Build a Shadowsocks service on your own
posts.text: Access be blocked by the GFW?Build a Shadowsocks service on your own If you dont want to read the introductions, go to Quick Start directlyCannot understand English? See Chinese edition here As President Xi came into power, the Internet access in China has become more and more restrictive. Most foreign websites are blocked in mainland China under the countrys policy of Internet censorship, which include Google, Youtube, Facebook, Twitter, Wikipedia (CN site) and so on. To visit these websites, you need to break through blockade of GFW. What is shadowsocks?Shadowsocks is an open-source encrypted proxy project, widely used in mainland China to circumvent Internet censorship. It was created in 2012 by a Chinese programmer named clowwindy, and multiple implementations of the protocol have been made available since. Typically, the client software will open a socks5 proxy on the machine it is run, which internet traffic can then be directed towards, similarly to an SSH tunnel. Unlike an SSH tunnel, shadowsocks can also proxy UDP traffic. There are several different types of shadowsocks now but all of them are based on socks5 protocol. (Read more in Wikipedia) What is the different between VPN and SS?Technically, shadowsocks has nothing to do with VPN. Its not a VPN, its a proxy. VPN is a virtual network interface which you can send everything through it. Proxy is a server used to forward data to another. There are two mainly difference between them. To use a proxy, you had to let program know there is a proxy. But you dont have to config programs to use VPN. You can transfer any kind of data through VPN. With proxy, only TCP can be delivered. (actually, in some version of shadowsocks, UDP also works) (Read more in this Quora) Why is a VPS needed?Look at the following picture. In the practical use, encrypted data is transferred through the VPS(SS Server) so that the GFW doesnt know where is the data from, and will naturally allow the data to pass through. Make sure these websites are accessible at the location of your VPS. Make sure the IP address of the VPS havent been blocked by the GFW. The shorter the distance between you location and the location of your VPS, the faster your Internet will be. Quick StartBuy a VPS BandweagonHost:        Official Website 1 (be blocked in China)        Official Website 2       Chinese Site (not official) Vultr Linode Digital Ocean Please check this link to get more information and suggestions If you know nothing about technology or have difficulty learning about it, please select BandweagonHost KVM versions. Remember to search for discount code before you pay. Install BBRThis step is optional but recommended, because it makes your VPS perform in a higher level. You dont need this step if you choose Quick install from BandweagonHost. See how to install in this article. Install shadowsocks on the VPSQuick install from BandweagonHost control panelBecause of some issues, new buyers cannot install ss from the panel automatically. If you dont have shadowsocks choice, go to Install from packet by  directly. Go to BWH services page and click on KiwiVM Control Panel. Click on the Stop button to shut down the VPS. And Click on the Install new OS button on the left. Choose one of CentOS-6 with bbr and reload it. After reloading, click on the Shadowsocks Server button on the left and Install Shadowsocks server. After completely installing, go back. Check the encryption method, server port and server password. Change them if you want. Install from packet by Reference - offical website of  Install Putty on your PC (In putty, right click the green box equals to paste, so no need to type word by word) Open Putty, enter IP address and SSH port of the VPS If its the first time youve configured the VPS, you may see a security alert. Just choose Yes when the alert occurs. When it says login in as:, enter root, and you can get the initial password through the KiwiVM control panel> Root password modification > Generate and set new root password After login in, you can enter passwd to reset the password as you want, then you dont have to remember the irregular password generated by the system. Make sure your VPS has wget command 1yum -y install wget Enter and configure as your need 123wget --no-check-certificate -O shadowsocks-all.sh https://raw.githubusercontent.com/teddysun/shadowsocks_install/master/shadowsocks-all.shchmod +x shadowsocks-all.sh./shadowsocks-all.sh 2>&1 | tee shadowsocks-all.log Successful if you get the following and record them: 123456Congratulations, your_shadowsocks_version install completed!Your Server IP :your_server_ipYour Server Port :your_server_portYour Password :your_passwordYour Encryption Method:your_encryption_method...... Multiuser configuration find your configuration file, the path might be /etc/shadowsocks.json, it actually depends the version of shadowsocks youve installed. So enter vi /etc/shadowsocks.json to edit the configuration file. Type i to enter the insert mode and write in the configuration file: 1234567891011121314{ "server":"0.0.0.0", #which indicates the ip of your VPS "local_address": "127.0.0.1", "local_port":1080, "port_password": { "8381": "password1", "8382": "password2", "8383": "password3", "8384": "password4" }, "timeout":300, "method":"aes-256-cfb", #change it if you need "fast_open": true} Change the ports and password to what you need Save it( esc+:wq ) and enter 12killall ssserverssserver -c /etc/shadowsocks.json -d start Download Client Shadowsocks Win MacOS X Android iOS Shadowsocks-R Win MacOS X Android iOS Input your SS service information (encryption method, server port and server password) and start enjoying the Internet without any restrictions. Other use of VPSIf you regard those red or green notes as s**t, just skip this step. But if you want to fully use the VPS you buy, you can download torrents, build a private cloud or even host a website on it.
